{{Use British English|date=June 2017}}
'''Christopher F. Clark''' is a British American [[historian]].

==Life==
He grew up in the [[London]] area.
He graduated from the [[University of Warwick]], and [[Harvard University]], with a PhD in History. 
He taught at the [[University of York]] for eighteen years, and at the [[University of Warwick]] for another seven years.  He teaches at the [[University of Connecticut]], since 2005.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.uconn.edu/people/clark.php |title=UCONN History &#124; People &#124; Christopher Clark |publisher=History.uconn.edu |date= |accessdate=2013-07-11}}</ref>

==Awards==
