'''Henryk Kocój''' (born 1931) is a Polish [[historian]]. Professor of the [[University of Silesia in Katowice|Silesian University]], he specializes in the Polish history of the 17th and 18th century, in particular, the history of the Constitution of 3 May, Great Sejm, and the partitions of [[Poland]].

