'''Hovann Simonian''' (born in [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]]) is an Armenian Swiss scholar in [[History of Armenia|Armenian history]], historical geography and culture.  Born in Beirut to Armenian parents, he was raised in [[Switzerland]] where his family moved at the beginning of the [[Lebanese Civil War|Civil War in Lebanon]] in 1975.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usanogh.com/content/view/418/93/ |title=Armenian DNA Project- Background |accessdate=2015-02-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110825022814/http://www.usanogh.com/content/view/418/93/ |archivedate=2011-08-25 |df= }}</ref>

He is the editor of ''[[Hemshin peoples|The Hemshin]]: History, Society and Identity in the Highlands of Northeast Turkey'' and co-author of ''Troubled Waters : the Geopolitics of the Caspian Region'' with [[Richard Dekmejian]]. He is also the administrator, along with Peter Hrechdakian and Mark Arslan, of the Armenian DNA Project.<ref>[https://www.loc.gov/today/pr/2014/14-051.html DNA and Armenian Origin Subject of 18th Annual Vardanants Day Lecture]</ref>

