'''Ramaprasad Chanda''' (15 August 1873 – 28 May 1942) was an [[India]]n historian and archaeologist from Bengal. A pioneer in his field in [[South Asia]], Chanda's lasting legacy is the [[Varendra Research Museum]], he established in Rajshahi (located in present-day [[Bangladesh]]), a leading institute  for research on the history of [[Bengal]].

==Publications==
* ''Gaudarajmala'', Rajshahi: Varendra Research Society (1912)
* ''Indo Aryan Races'', Rajshahi: Varendra Research Society (1916)
* ''Letters and Documents Relating to the Life of Raja Rammohan Roy''

